status_message: Blade and Passenger 57 star Wesley Snipes has been ordered to serve a three-year prison sentence for failing to file his income tax returns.
Prince William and Kate Middleton have given their support to an extra bank holiday that would allow the country to mark their wedding day.

Hate preacher Abu Hamza has won his appeal against the Government's attempts to
strip him of his British passport, the Special Immigration Appeals Commission
(Siac) has announced.

All 68 people on board an AeroCaribbean plane have been killed after it crashed in mountainous central Cuba.
http://news.sky.com/skynews/Home/World-News/Cuba-Passenger-Plane-With-68-People-on-Board-Crashes-Authorities-Say-No-One-Has-Survived/Article/201011115795483?lpos=World_News_Carousel_Region_1&lid=ARTICLE_15795483_Cuba%3A_Passenger_Plane_With_68_People_on_Board_Crashes%2C_Authorities_Say_No_One_Has_Survived
Paul the octopus, who won unlikely worldwide fame correctly predicting a host of World Cup matches, has died, apparently of natural causes.
JLS win Best Album and Best UK Act at the 15th annual MOBO awards, while Tinie Tempah takes Best Newcomer and Best Video for Frisky.
Jean-Claude Van Damme denies suffering a heart attack on the set of his latest film, saying he is "100% healthy and training well".
National Lottery operator Camelot says the £113m EuroMillions jackpot from the draw on October 8 has now been claimed.
A gay Saudi Prince is facing a life sentence for beating and strangling his servant to death in the culmination of a campaign of "sadistic" abuse.
The amount of pension savings on which people receive a tax break is to be cut from £255,000 to £50,000 from next April to save £4bn a year.
History's longest underground ordeal ends at 69 days: Last trapped Chile miner reaches surface
A sea lion has attacked a college rowing boat in New Zealand and chased the panicked crew to shore.

Over two-thirds of the 33 miners trapped for more than two months in Chile's San 
Jose mine have been rescued. Watch Sky News for LIVE coverage.
21st miner Yonni Barrios emerges from mine to the welcome of his mistress, but not his wife.
Yonni Barrios will be 21st miner to be rescued; his wife learnt of his affair while he was underground.
Tenth Chilean miner Alex Richard Vega Salazar reaches surface of San Jose mine.
Ed Miliband takes part in first PMQs since becoming Labour leader.
Ninth Chilean miner Mario Gomez Heredia reaches surface.
Union sources: Banking giant Lloyds is to axe 4,500 jobs and move work abroad.
The Commonwealth Games is facing a new crisis amid reports that several swimmers have a stomach virus potentially caused by the quality of water in New Delhi.

Dry, with some sun for most areas. Cloudier in Scotland, with a chance of showers. Cloudy in southern England later on. Patchy rain possible
.
France has become the latest country to warn travellers to Britain of the heightened risk of a terrorist attack.
Liverpool chairman Martin Broughton tells Sky News the club will be sold to New England Sports Ventures, the owner of the Boston Red Sox, for £300m.
Liverpool Football Club confirms it has agreed to sell the club to New England Sports Ventures, the parent company of the Boston Red Sox.
Prince William carries out his first RAF search & rescue mission, his Sea King helicopter picking up a seriously ill gas worker from a rig in Morecambe Bay.
Ex-Paris trader Jerome Kerviel found guilty of fraud, jailed for three years and told to repay Societe Generale the £4.2bn the bank lost.
Two people arrested on suspicion of arson after Hastings Pier was severely damaged by fire, East Sussex Fire & Rescue Service announces.
Home Secretary Theresa May authorises blanket ban on marches in Leicester on October 9 amid a planned protest by the English Defence League.
Welcome!
Sky News wins RTS News Channel of the Year for the seventh time.
Sky News wins four awards, including Best News Service at the Broadcast Digital Awards.
Sky News wins six awards, including RTS News Channel of the Year for the sixth time.
Sky News wins six awards from the Royal Television Society, including News Channel of the Year and Television Journalist of the Year - Dominic Waghorn.

Sky News wins RTS Innovation Award; Best News Channel, Digital Channel Awards; Golden Nymph Award for Best News Programme; International Emmy Award for Breaking News for coverage of the July 7th bombings. Jeremy Thompson wins RTS News Presenter of the Year.
Sky News wins RTS News Channel of the Year for the fourth time.
Sky News wins RTS News Channel of the year for the third time.
Sky News wins BAFTA News Award for coverage of the Soham murders and the RTS News Channel of the Year.

Sky News wins BAFTA News Award for reporting of 9/11; RTS News Channel of the Year and the Guardian Edinburgh International Television Festival Non-Terrestrial Channel of the Year. Adam Boulton, political editor, receives RTS Judges award
Sky News wins Best Innovation Online Journalism Award for Online Pop-Up Papers in the NetMedia Awards for European Online Journalism
Sky News wins RTS award for Kosovo coverage
Sky News wins Cable Guide Favourite News Channel for the second year running.
Sky News wins Cable Guide Favourite News Channel
Sky News wins an Emmy for its coverage of South Africa
